      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Dec 8 /84 ¶ MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew. ¶ My dear Baron ¶  ¶ If I do not answer a letter at once I do not know when I may! so I break off my work at ¶  ¶ Alternanthera nodiflora ¶  ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.12.08a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by M: 'Answ. 5/2/85 FvM'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Dec 8 /84<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I do not answer a letter at once I do not know when I may! so I break off my work at<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Alternanthera nodiflora</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; A sessilis to thank you for your just opened, &amp; read, of 23/10/84<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to J. Hooker, 23 October 1884.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; its most interesting enclosures from Dr Scortechini<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">!</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— (What a name for an Italian<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">!</hi>
               </seg>).<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The words 'Scortechini' and 'Italian' have been underlined and a large exclamation mark pencilled in the margin against this section. In Italian, the verb<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">scortecciare</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>means to strip the bark off!</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— I need hardly say I shall be delighted to see him &amp; give him all assistance here, &amp; shall urge his publishing his new species with all despatch. I shall indeed be only too glad of his help in that way. As to subsidies, that we must attack Sr H. Lowe<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir Hugh Low.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for — He has returned already I believe.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With your letter came a very interesting one from Consul Sandwich of Crete to whom I had written about the Evergreen Plant that Pliny mentions<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Natural History</seg>, book 12 v. 11: ‘est Gortynae in insula Creta iuxta fintem platanus una insignis utriusque linguae monimentis, numquam folia dimittens’. [There is a single plane-tree at the side of a spring at Gortyn in the island of Crete which is celebrated in records written both in Greek and Latin, as never shedding its leaves.] The Evergreen plane, described in 1908 as the species<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Platanus cretica,</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has since also been treated as a variety,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">P. orientalis</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>var<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">cretica.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; of which he sends me leaves &amp; fruit, the latter differing considerably from the common P.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">orientalis</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are busy at the Herbarium about getting up a Catalogue of Chinese plants by Mr Forbes<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Francis Blackwell Forbes.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The first part of F. Forbes &amp; Hemsley (1886-1888) was issued<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>20<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>May 1886 (TL2).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who has spent some years there (not the Timor laut<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; N. Guinea man<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Ogg Forbes; for Timor-laut<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(now Kepulauan Tanimbar, Indonesia)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see H. Forbes (1885), pp. 307 ff.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>) — a merchant, &amp; for which we have a small grant from the R.S.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Society.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It will be most useful.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am printing<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Labiatae</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of Flora B. I.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker (1875-97).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; preparing Amaranthaceae for press, but I am so distracted with Councils &amp; Committees, official &amp; unofficial, in London, that what with these &amp; Garden work, &amp; my family duties, I am hard pressed to get on.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever most sincerely your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have two parcels of plants to thank you for[.] Oliver is busy with them.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Alternanthera nodiflora</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Alternanthera sessilis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Amaranthaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Labiatae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Platanus orientalis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
